1
00:00:58,601 --> 00:00:59,435
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

2
00:00:59,518 --> 00:01:01,020
CHILDREN WERE FILMED SAFELY
GEN AI WAS USED FOR SOME SCENES

3
00:01:02,688 --> 00:01:04,857
The bigger my feelings for you get…

4
00:01:05,566 --> 00:01:08,486
the smaller I feel.

5
00:01:11,989 --> 00:01:14,784
Why do I have to shoulder your past too?

6
00:01:19,121 --> 00:01:20,039
I'm sorry…

7
00:01:22,708 --> 00:01:24,794
that I'm just not as strong as you.

8
00:01:43,521 --> 00:01:46,273
I never tried to stop anyone from leaving.

9
00:01:47,066 --> 00:01:49,777
I always respected their decision.

10
00:01:51,070 --> 00:01:52,696
That was my way of caring
for the other person

11
00:01:53,531 --> 00:01:55,574
and protecting my pride.

12
00:02:01,038 --> 00:02:02,832
But this time, I can't do that.

13
00:02:36,532 --> 00:02:38,993
Even if I end up broken and pathetic…

14
00:02:41,829 --> 00:02:44,874
I don't want to lose this person.

15
00:02:50,379 --> 00:02:54,425
EPISODE 9
THERE'S AN ERROR, STILL CLOCKING IN!

16
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:53,836
I feel one way one second
and another way the next.

17
00:04:53,919 --> 00:04:55,629
Even I can't keep up with my own feelings.

18
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,007
So who could keep up with--

19
00:05:00,676 --> 00:05:01,635
Be careful.

20
00:05:15,691 --> 00:05:17,901
Don't you resent me at all?

21
00:05:19,278 --> 00:05:21,905
After all the awful things I said to you?

22
00:05:27,995 --> 00:05:30,622
I do resent you.
You said the most hurtful words.

23
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,374
It's not like I'm a saint.

24
00:05:32,958 --> 00:05:34,334
Then why are you following me?

25
00:05:34,418 --> 00:05:36,962
Because I like you more than I resent you.

26
00:05:38,297 --> 00:05:39,840
The least I can do is take you home.

27
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:41,133
I'm…

28
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:46,805
not sure if I can keep liking you.

29
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:50,267
I know.

30
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:54,605
And I can't promise something like this
won't ever happen again.

31
00:05:55,272 --> 00:05:57,775
So you're saying this could happen again.

32
00:05:57,858 --> 00:05:59,943
Just like I can't change my past,

33
00:06:00,027 --> 00:06:02,112
things can happen out of my control.

34
00:06:03,739 --> 00:06:07,117
Still, I want to make sure you trust me
enough to not be swayed by them.

35
00:06:08,577 --> 00:06:09,578
I don't know

36
00:06:10,621 --> 00:06:13,207
if I'd be able to trust you
no matter what happens.

37
00:06:17,294 --> 00:06:19,588
Why were you late today?

38
00:06:20,589 --> 00:06:23,801
Ms. Choi's mother suddenly collapsed.

39
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,761
-Is she all right?
-Yes.

40
00:06:25,844 --> 00:06:27,888
She was moved to the hospital
and recovered shortly after.

41
00:06:29,598 --> 00:06:30,432
Whatever the reason,

42
00:06:30,516 --> 00:06:33,435
I'm sorry I ended up
leaving you by yourself today.

43
00:06:36,313 --> 00:06:37,648
I need

44
00:06:38,607 --> 00:06:40,150
some time right now.

45
00:06:40,734 --> 00:06:41,819
Okay, then.

46
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:44,696
I'll just keep on liking you
like I have all along.

47
00:06:44,780 --> 00:06:45,781
Mr. Kang.

48
00:06:51,662 --> 00:06:53,038
Take all the time you need to think.

49
00:06:53,122 --> 00:06:55,415
I'll stay by your side

50
00:06:55,499 --> 00:06:58,168
and won't go anywhere,
just like I promised you.

51
00:06:59,044 --> 00:07:01,922
But what if I say I want to end things?

52
00:07:02,005 --> 00:07:04,049
Then I'll try to do even better.

53
00:07:04,133 --> 00:07:06,885
What if I still say I can't do this?

54
00:07:07,553 --> 00:07:10,139
Then there's nothing I can do.
I'll have to give up.

55
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:16,353
But it won't be easy to turn me down…

56
00:07:18,355 --> 00:07:21,275
because I plan on liking you
with everything I've got.

57
00:07:26,738 --> 00:07:28,657
I'll stop following you now and get going.

58
00:07:29,658 --> 00:07:31,827
It's cold, so go on in.

59
00:07:54,975 --> 00:07:57,895
WE'RE A TEAM

60
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:06,111
Good night.

61
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:34,056
Hey, let's take a break.

62
00:08:34,139 --> 00:08:36,099
Come on, take a break.

63
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:40,187
That's what you get
for tagging along when you never run.

64
00:08:40,938 --> 00:08:44,149
I got curious because literally everyone
is running these days.

65
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:47,069
But I can't do this. It's too exhausting.

66
00:08:56,078 --> 00:08:58,288
It's the weekend.
Aren't you seeing Ms. Ji-yoon?

67
00:08:59,581 --> 00:09:00,791
I'm waiting on her.

68
00:09:00,874 --> 00:09:01,917
Figures.

69
00:09:02,751 --> 00:09:04,336
Everyone's got a date except me.

70
00:09:08,257 --> 00:09:09,466
I moved yesterday.

71
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,636
What is it?

72
00:09:13,428 --> 00:09:14,888
Did Ms. Ji-yoon bail on you today?

73
00:09:16,473 --> 00:09:17,391
It's my father.

74
00:09:18,058 --> 00:09:19,601
He moved to a new place yesterday.

75
00:09:19,685 --> 00:09:20,686
Already?

76
00:09:22,521 --> 00:09:24,439
Still telling you after the fact, huh?

77
00:09:27,401 --> 00:09:28,527
Shouldn't you go visit him?

78
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:31,238
It's not that easy.

79
00:09:32,322 --> 00:09:33,865
Do you still blame your father?

80
00:09:35,242 --> 00:09:36,618
At my age? Come on.

81
00:09:36,702 --> 00:09:39,413
Your whole life got rebooted
because of him.

82
00:09:40,122 --> 00:09:41,456
It's okay to hold a grudge.

83
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:43,333
I definitely felt that way back then,

84
00:09:44,126 --> 00:09:45,085
but now?

85
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:48,046
It's like a scab.

86
00:09:48,839 --> 00:09:50,132
It doesn't hurt

87
00:09:50,882 --> 00:09:52,092
or even itch.

88
00:09:52,843 --> 00:09:54,720
That actually sounds worse, you know.

89
00:09:55,387 --> 00:09:56,346
Maybe.

90
00:09:57,431 --> 00:09:58,849
Here's your chicken.

91
00:10:01,935 --> 00:10:04,229
You ordered fried chicken? You?

92
00:10:04,313 --> 00:10:05,605
For lunch, at that?

93
00:10:05,689 --> 00:10:09,109
Ms. Ji-yoon likes it,
so I'm trying to get into it too.

94
00:10:11,695 --> 00:10:13,196
And you still go for the breast meat.

95
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:22,914
When someone says they need time,

96
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,125
how much space should I give them?

97
00:10:25,208 --> 00:10:26,209
Did Ms. Ji-yoon say that?

98
00:10:26,293 --> 00:10:27,127
Yeah.

99
00:10:27,753 --> 00:10:28,587
Huh.

100
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:30,255
At long last,

101
00:10:31,006 --> 00:10:32,841
I get a chance to give you advice.

102
00:10:34,509 --> 00:10:35,469
I'll hear you out at least.

103
00:10:38,597 --> 00:10:41,224
Even if she said she needs time,

104
00:10:41,308 --> 00:10:42,517
you shouldn't leave her all alone.

105
00:10:42,601 --> 00:10:45,395
You also can't cling so much
that you get on her nerves.

106
00:10:45,479 --> 00:10:47,898
You're just there
when she happens to look back,

107
00:10:47,981 --> 00:10:50,984
wandering close by
with a different vibe than usual

108
00:10:51,985 --> 00:10:53,028
and soulful eyes.

109
00:10:54,613 --> 00:10:55,447
Isn't that stalking?

110
00:10:55,530 --> 00:10:57,908
Come on, you're so dry.

111
00:10:57,991 --> 00:10:59,743
You know you can't just cut off contact

112
00:10:59,826 --> 00:11:01,787
just because she asked for time, right?

113
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:04,956
You still have to check in
every morning and every night.

114
00:11:05,040 --> 00:11:06,792
And end your texts with a question mark.

115
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,126
A question mark?

116
00:11:08,210 --> 00:11:09,419
Oh, come on.

117
00:11:09,503 --> 00:11:12,506
That's the only way
to keep the conversation going.

118
00:11:14,299 --> 00:11:16,259
Enough. I'll figure it out myself.

119
00:11:16,343 --> 00:11:18,303
Why? I've got tons more tips.

120
00:11:18,387 --> 00:11:19,638
Just eat.

121
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:27,854
One second.

122
00:11:28,897 --> 00:11:29,731
Why's everyone here?

123
00:11:37,906 --> 00:11:39,783
-What's going on?
-Na-ri wanted to show off.

124
00:11:39,866 --> 00:11:40,700
Show off what?

125
00:11:40,784 --> 00:11:42,369
Mr. Kang!

126
00:11:42,452 --> 00:11:43,286
Look.

127
00:11:44,079 --> 00:11:46,456
Doesn't Mr. Kang look
totally amazing today?

128
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:49,209
He looks so much younger
with his hair down like that.

129
00:11:49,292 --> 00:11:50,794
And his outfit!

130
00:11:50,877 --> 00:11:52,587
He's got that boyfriend look today.

131
00:11:53,547 --> 00:11:55,173
-He's so handsome.
-He looks younger.

132
00:11:55,257 --> 00:11:58,343
I'm going to head out.
You two go on in and enjoy the view.

133
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:05,892
Hey, morning.

134
00:12:31,293 --> 00:12:34,171
You know you can't just cut off contact
just because she asked for time, right?

135
00:12:34,254 --> 00:12:37,132
You still have to check in
every morning and every night.

136
00:12:37,716 --> 00:12:39,301
And end your texts with a question mark.

137
00:12:51,438 --> 00:12:52,481
KANG SI-WOO

138
00:12:52,564 --> 00:12:53,690
Good morning?

139
00:13:08,455 --> 00:13:10,165
I knew it. Wrong answer again.

140
00:13:13,668 --> 00:13:14,544
Ms. Cha.

141
00:13:17,172 --> 00:13:18,215
Do you have a moment?

142
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:33,230
Why aren't you saying anything
about this photo?

143
00:13:35,398 --> 00:13:36,233
What about it?

144
00:13:37,150 --> 00:13:38,109
Look closely.

145
00:13:38,193 --> 00:13:40,820
Mr. Kang and Ms. Choi Soo-jin
used to be married!

146
00:13:40,904 --> 00:13:42,531
Yeah, so?

147
00:13:42,614 --> 00:13:44,908
How is their history any of your business?

148
00:13:44,991 --> 00:13:47,285
The whole company
will flip out if this gets out.

149
00:13:47,369 --> 00:13:48,995
It'll be a scandal like no other!

150
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:51,581
Yeah?

151
00:13:52,207 --> 00:13:53,750
DELETE THIS IMAGE?
YES

152
00:13:55,418 --> 00:13:57,045
Then just pretend you never saw it.

153
00:13:57,921 --> 00:13:58,797
You knew, didn't you?

154
00:14:01,675 --> 00:14:04,261
Well, how did you
even find out about this?

155
00:14:04,970 --> 00:14:06,137
By chance.

156
00:14:06,221 --> 00:14:09,015
It won't do us any favors
if Mr. Kang gets into a mess.

157
00:14:09,975 --> 00:14:11,726
The demo's coming up soon,

158
00:14:12,394 --> 00:14:13,603
so don't stir things up.

159
00:14:24,698 --> 00:14:26,241
Are the brochures ready?

160
00:14:26,324 --> 00:14:28,952
There were a few rounds of edits,
and now they're off to print.

161
00:14:29,035 --> 00:14:30,245
What about living appliances?

162
00:14:30,328 --> 00:14:31,413
All good.

163
00:14:31,496 --> 00:14:32,831
Are the kitchen appliances done?

164
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:35,375
-Yes.
-How's the integration program?

165
00:14:35,458 --> 00:14:36,960
It's done, and we're running tests.

166
00:14:37,794 --> 00:14:41,381
Okay, then what's left
is the most important part of Home-AI.

167
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:44,092
There's still something left?

168
00:14:46,928 --> 00:14:47,762
Trust.

169
00:14:49,723 --> 00:14:51,725
Just as trust is essential between people,

170
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:54,894
if there isn't trust
between people and AI,

171
00:14:54,978 --> 00:14:56,354
this project will fail.

172
00:14:57,689 --> 00:15:00,317
-Are you talking about security?
-Yes.

173
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,318
But how?

174
00:15:02,277 --> 00:15:04,446
There's not much time until the demo.

175
00:15:04,529 --> 00:15:07,198
I've been looking
for a security solution for a long time.

176
00:15:07,282 --> 00:15:10,660
Is that what all those secret meetings
with the President were about?

177
00:15:11,411 --> 00:15:12,245
Yes.

178
00:15:12,829 --> 00:15:15,081
So, did you find the answer?

179
00:15:15,665 --> 00:15:17,208
I'm still working on it.

180
00:15:26,718 --> 00:15:27,719
But don't worry.

181
00:15:28,970 --> 00:15:30,639
I'll have it solved before the demo.

182
00:15:31,973 --> 00:15:33,892
Everyone, let's run our final checks now.

183
00:15:33,975 --> 00:15:34,934
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

184
00:16:05,340 --> 00:16:06,174
S W
ENTER YOUR PIN

185
00:16:06,257 --> 00:16:07,092
INCORRECT PIN

186
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:11,388
LONGLIVESAEUM
INCORRECT PIN

187
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:18,561
Interesting taste.

188
00:16:35,245 --> 00:16:36,162
We did it, sir!

189
00:16:36,246 --> 00:16:38,164
We just got approval
for a regulatory sandbox!

190
00:16:38,248 --> 00:16:39,416
Really?

191
00:16:39,499 --> 00:16:40,792
Then let's jump right in!

192
00:16:40,875 --> 00:16:44,295
If we push hard, we can showcase it
at the task force's demo.

193
00:16:45,588 --> 00:16:46,965
You can work late tonight, right?

194
00:16:48,842 --> 00:16:49,676
Yes.

195
00:16:59,394 --> 00:17:00,478
I'm sorry.

196
00:17:00,562 --> 00:17:03,314
I just got hit with overtime,
so I'll have to cancel our plans.

197
00:17:03,398 --> 00:17:04,482
Sorry.

198
00:17:05,817 --> 00:17:08,486
And he must've been
so hyped for our first date.

199
00:17:09,988 --> 00:17:12,031
You can't go on a date because of work?

200
00:17:14,117 --> 00:17:14,951
That's super cool!

201
00:17:16,411 --> 00:17:17,620
Weird thing to find cool.

202
00:17:18,830 --> 00:17:20,540
I'll call you when I'm done.

203
00:17:21,666 --> 00:17:22,792
Okay. You got this, No-ah!

204
00:17:47,817 --> 00:17:48,693
Holy cow.

205
00:17:49,444 --> 00:17:50,403
What's wrong?

206
00:17:50,487 --> 00:17:53,072
Forget AI.
My integrity just got totally shattered.

207
00:17:54,032 --> 00:17:56,868
Is it your loan interest?
Is it not taken care of yet?

208
00:17:57,535 --> 00:17:59,412
It's even worse than that.

209
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:04,125
What on earth have I done?

210
00:18:13,009 --> 00:18:13,843
Are you clocking out?

211
00:18:14,594 --> 00:18:15,428
Yes.

212
00:18:16,471 --> 00:18:17,305
And you?

213
00:18:24,646 --> 00:18:25,688
Get in.

214
00:18:40,411 --> 00:18:41,538
Where are you going?

215
00:18:42,413 --> 00:18:43,998
I'm going to see you off.

216
00:18:47,544 --> 00:18:48,670
Don't worry,

217
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:51,214
I'm only escorting you to the first floor.

218
00:18:51,798 --> 00:18:53,967
You really don't need to do this.

219
00:18:54,843 --> 00:18:57,095
I can't change the past,

220
00:18:57,178 --> 00:18:58,847
but I can change the present,
don't you think?

221
00:19:00,515 --> 00:19:03,101
I'll keep trying until you can trust me,

222
00:19:03,184 --> 00:19:04,143
Ms. Ji-yoon.

223
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:12,277
It's your leg that's broken,

224
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:14,696
so why do you want me to wash your hair?

225
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:18,032
I can't believe I have to
wait on my husband hand and foot.

226
00:19:19,617 --> 00:19:20,535
What are you doing?

227
00:19:21,035 --> 00:19:22,078
Hey, kid.

228
00:19:26,916 --> 00:19:29,168
You go and dry your dad's hair.

229
00:19:33,423 --> 00:19:35,133
You can't even wash your own hair?

230
00:19:38,761 --> 00:19:40,346
I can if I have to.

231
00:19:41,723 --> 00:19:42,599
Then what is it?

232
00:19:44,058 --> 00:19:45,143
I was playing it up a bit.

233
00:19:46,394 --> 00:19:47,228
Enjoying yourself?

234
00:19:47,979 --> 00:19:49,188
I'm having a blast.

235
00:19:52,066 --> 00:19:54,694
Stop peeling. You'll wear yourself out.

236
00:19:54,777 --> 00:19:58,406
You should've just bought
the prepped ones in the first place.

237
00:19:58,489 --> 00:20:00,700
They don't measure up. They're wilted
and come in small portions.

238
00:20:01,284 --> 00:20:04,787
Then did you choose Dad
because he "measured up" from day one?

239
00:20:12,337 --> 00:20:13,796
Where was that again?

240
00:20:14,339 --> 00:20:16,507
I swear it was around here somewhere.

241
00:20:19,928 --> 00:20:21,095
Obviously.

242
00:20:21,179 --> 00:20:23,806
There was no man who could
compare to your dad back then.

243
00:20:23,890 --> 00:20:24,724
Really?

244
00:20:25,308 --> 00:20:26,434
What did you like about him?

245
00:20:26,517 --> 00:20:27,977
He never talked nonsense

246
00:20:28,061 --> 00:20:29,646
and always kept his word.

247
00:20:29,729 --> 00:20:31,230
It's not easy to live like that.

248
00:20:31,314 --> 00:20:33,441
I thought he was someone I could trust.

249
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:38,029
So?

250
00:20:38,988 --> 00:20:39,822
What about now?

251
00:20:39,906 --> 00:20:43,117
He doesn't say anything,
so there's no word for him to keep.

252
00:20:43,993 --> 00:20:46,204
Just wait and see on that part.

253
00:20:46,287 --> 00:20:47,997
I'll waste all my years just waiting.

254
00:20:48,581 --> 00:20:51,709
I was washing his hair earlier,
and he's got so much gray hair.

255
00:20:52,585 --> 00:20:54,045
When did he get so old?

256
00:20:55,380 --> 00:20:58,174
Don't let your precious time just slip by.
Make it count, okay?

257
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:00,134
Okay.

258
00:21:04,472 --> 00:21:05,515
Mom,

259
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:09,602
what kind of person
do you want me to end up with?

260
00:21:09,686 --> 00:21:11,229
Well, I'd like someone

261
00:21:12,647 --> 00:21:15,733
who puts up with you no matter
how much attitude you throw around.

262
00:21:15,817 --> 00:21:17,986
When do I ever throw an attitude?

263
00:21:18,069 --> 00:21:21,155
I mean, I'd like someone
who loves you that deeply.

264
00:21:21,739 --> 00:21:22,782
If his love for you is deep,

265
00:21:23,408 --> 00:21:25,368
you'll be able to overcome
the rough waves.

266
00:21:29,497 --> 00:21:30,790
Take all the time you need to think.

267
00:21:31,582 --> 00:21:34,836
I'll just keep on liking you
like I have all along.

268
00:21:40,758 --> 00:21:42,677
Seriously, I told you not to come out.

269
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:45,179
I have to move a little
if I want to recover faster.

270
00:21:45,263 --> 00:21:46,347
I'll just go this far.

271
00:21:47,932 --> 00:21:49,058
Dad.

272
00:21:49,142 --> 00:21:49,976
Yeah?

273
00:21:50,727 --> 00:21:52,979
You know the guy
who fixed my cassette player?

274
00:21:53,813 --> 00:21:54,647
What's he like?

275
00:21:54,731 --> 00:21:56,941
Why? Is it not working right?

276
00:21:57,025 --> 00:21:59,444
No, I'm just grateful to him.

277
00:22:00,653 --> 00:22:02,321
He fixed my stuff so well,

278
00:22:02,405 --> 00:22:04,365
keeps you company,

279
00:22:04,449 --> 00:22:05,825
and even got you a gift.

280
00:22:07,326 --> 00:22:08,536
He's a decent kid.

281
00:22:10,246 --> 00:22:11,748
And a lonely one.

282
00:22:13,207 --> 00:22:14,042
Why?

283
00:22:14,792 --> 00:22:17,628
Look at how your mom washed my hair today.

284
00:22:18,838 --> 00:22:20,923
No matter how pathetic
or useless you become,

285
00:22:21,841 --> 00:22:23,634
your family sticks with you in the end.

286
00:22:25,970 --> 00:22:27,472
But that kid?

287
00:22:28,681 --> 00:22:29,932
He's on his own.

288
00:22:30,016 --> 00:22:32,143
I don't know the whole story,

289
00:22:32,643 --> 00:22:34,020
but his mother passed away,

290
00:22:34,103 --> 00:22:36,272
he has barely any contact with his father,

291
00:22:38,191 --> 00:22:39,650
and I think he had a failed marriage.

292
00:22:41,486 --> 00:22:42,528
That's rough.

293
00:22:44,322 --> 00:22:46,949
Even so, he's solid to the bone.

294
00:22:47,784 --> 00:22:50,244
He's grown into a very fine man.

295
00:22:51,496 --> 00:22:55,249
His parents would've been very proud
if they'd been by his side.

296
00:22:58,628 --> 00:23:01,339
What would you think
if I dated someone like that?

297
00:23:03,257 --> 00:23:04,092
Huh?

298
00:23:05,301 --> 00:23:06,511
Just what I said.

299
00:23:10,765 --> 00:23:11,724
I'm not sure.

300
00:23:11,808 --> 00:23:14,727
You said he's a good guy.
Why are you hesitating?

301
00:23:14,811 --> 00:23:17,021
That's a whole different issue.

302
00:23:18,189 --> 00:23:20,233
To me,
no matter how impressive the guy is,

303
00:23:20,316 --> 00:23:21,901
you'll always be too good for him.

304
00:23:23,111 --> 00:23:23,945
Geez.

305
00:23:24,654 --> 00:23:26,572
Head inside now. Mom must be waiting.

306
00:23:26,656 --> 00:23:28,783
Right, I can't have your mom worrying.

307
00:23:28,866 --> 00:23:29,826
Get home safe.

308
00:23:29,909 --> 00:23:31,077
-See you.
-Yeah.

309
00:23:35,623 --> 00:23:36,707
Mr. Jeon.

310
00:23:36,791 --> 00:23:38,000
You've been working until now?

311
00:23:38,084 --> 00:23:39,502
Working and thinking over stuff.

312
00:23:40,128 --> 00:23:41,087
Thinking over what?

313
00:23:45,258 --> 00:23:47,343
Is Ji-yoon seeing anyone right now?

314
00:23:48,553 --> 00:23:49,387
Why do you ask?

315
00:23:51,389 --> 00:23:52,640
I think it's someone I know.

316
00:23:54,934 --> 00:23:56,477
Huh? Why? What is it?

317
00:23:56,561 --> 00:23:57,436
Hey!

318
00:23:58,187 --> 00:23:59,230
How did you know?

319
00:23:59,313 --> 00:24:01,816
Well, they have the same sticker and…

320
00:24:03,651 --> 00:24:04,485
You knew too?

321
00:24:05,111 --> 00:24:06,445
I told her to be careful.

322
00:24:07,071 --> 00:24:07,905
So?

323
00:24:08,656 --> 00:24:10,074
-Did you let on that you know?
-No.

324
00:24:11,909 --> 00:24:12,952
But I think

325
00:24:13,786 --> 00:24:15,913
things are bad between them
because of my mistake.

326
00:24:15,997 --> 00:24:16,956
What should I do?

327
00:24:17,456 --> 00:24:18,875
What kind of mistake?

328
00:24:18,958 --> 00:24:20,126
I really can't tell you that.

329
00:24:21,586 --> 00:24:22,920
I don't know what it is, but…

330
00:24:23,004 --> 00:24:24,797
I should apologize first, right?

331
00:24:24,881 --> 00:24:27,175
No, just act like you don't know anything.

332
00:24:27,550 --> 00:24:28,384
What?

333
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:31,095
If they realize you've caught on,
it could get even messier.

334
00:24:31,679 --> 00:24:33,222
It's up to them to sort things out.

335
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:35,558
Right.

336
00:24:36,934 --> 00:24:38,936
-You think so?
-Yes. Let's leave.

337
00:24:42,398 --> 00:24:44,275
They lied to me. Well, not exactly lied.

338
00:24:44,358 --> 00:24:45,193
No-ah!

339
00:24:51,782 --> 00:24:52,700
Who's this?

340
00:24:52,783 --> 00:24:54,452
He's my… cousin.

341
00:24:57,288 --> 00:24:58,122
Yes.

342
00:25:00,333 --> 00:25:01,751
It's late. I'll get going.

343
00:25:02,335 --> 00:25:03,169
Bye.

344
00:25:08,424 --> 00:25:10,509
How long have you been waiting?

345
00:25:11,135 --> 00:25:12,470
You should've called me.

346
00:25:13,638 --> 00:25:14,680
"Cousin"?

347
00:25:16,140 --> 00:25:17,683
Are you embarrassed about dating me?

348
00:25:17,767 --> 00:25:19,602
No, it's not that.

349
00:25:21,395 --> 00:25:23,940
It just gets messy
if you share your private life at work.

350
00:25:26,442 --> 00:25:27,276
Sorry.

351
00:25:28,110 --> 00:25:30,279
Keeping things secret is a habit of mine.

352
00:25:31,906 --> 00:25:34,242
I'm really sorry, okay?

353
00:25:36,327 --> 00:25:39,789
One iced Americano
and one hot café latte, please.

354
00:25:40,456 --> 00:25:41,457
It's on me.

355
00:25:41,540 --> 00:25:43,793
No, come on. You're a student.

356
00:25:43,876 --> 00:25:45,544
A slice of cheesecake as well, please.

357
00:25:51,175 --> 00:25:52,301
Open wide.

358
00:25:54,762 --> 00:25:55,888
You got something here.

359
00:25:57,890 --> 00:25:58,808
One moment, please.

360
00:26:06,565 --> 00:26:08,776
We could've stopped by your place first.

361
00:26:08,859 --> 00:26:10,486
Why? You wanted to pay for the cab too?

362
00:26:10,569 --> 00:26:11,696
Of course, I should--

363
00:26:11,779 --> 00:26:12,697
No-ah.

364
00:26:13,155 --> 00:26:13,990
Yes?

365
00:26:18,035 --> 00:26:19,328
Don't treat me like a child.

366
00:26:20,121 --> 00:26:20,955
What?

367
00:26:44,103 --> 00:26:45,688
Would a child do something like that?

368
00:26:47,481 --> 00:26:49,650
Hey, I never…

369
00:26:49,734 --> 00:26:50,860
I'll call you when I'm home.

370
00:27:23,809 --> 00:27:26,020
GOOD NIGHT

371
00:27:29,357 --> 00:27:30,858
What should I say?

372
00:27:34,904 --> 00:27:36,322
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME HELP?

373
00:27:38,532 --> 00:27:40,659
I need a goodnight message

374
00:27:40,743 --> 00:27:43,079
that really shows my girlfriend
how much I like her.

375
00:27:43,162 --> 00:27:44,205
In text form.

376
00:27:45,164 --> 00:27:48,250
STAY BY MY SIDE EVEN IN YOUR DREAMS!
GOOD NIGHT, MY LOVE

377
00:27:50,002 --> 00:27:53,130
You've lived with me this long,
and you still haven't figured me out?

378
00:28:02,848 --> 00:28:05,476
YOU'RE ALL I THINK OF AT THE END OF MY DAY
YOU'RE THE GREATEST GIFT IN MY LIFE

379
00:28:05,559 --> 00:28:07,561
SWEET DREAMS,
AND HAVE A GREAT START OF THE DAY TOMORROW

380
00:28:07,645 --> 00:28:08,479
I LOVE YOU SO VERY MUCH!

381
00:28:09,397 --> 00:28:10,773
That's seriously the worst.

382
00:28:22,451 --> 00:28:23,828
I still like you a lot today.

383
00:28:24,912 --> 00:28:25,830
Good night.

384
00:28:28,416 --> 00:28:29,458
Well, that's unexpected.

385
00:28:31,544 --> 00:28:33,170
But it won't be easy to turn me down

386
00:28:33,754 --> 00:28:36,549
because I plan on liking you
with everything I've got.

387
00:29:08,914 --> 00:29:09,957
Good morning!

388
00:29:22,553 --> 00:29:24,597
RESTAURANT OZ - RESERVATION REMINDER
PARTY OF 2

389
00:29:34,440 --> 00:29:35,608
The restaurant

390
00:29:35,691 --> 00:29:38,277
we booked today, should we cancel…

391
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:39,195
Yes, President Han.

392
00:29:41,071 --> 00:29:42,490
Can we push it to next time?

393
00:29:43,115 --> 00:29:44,200
I have plans tonight.

394
00:29:47,286 --> 00:29:48,120
Yes, ma'am.

395
00:30:09,767 --> 00:30:11,185
Why are you so quiet?

396
00:30:11,268 --> 00:30:12,770
Are you even doing what I asked?

397
00:30:15,189 --> 00:30:18,067
Actually, I did find out something,

398
00:30:18,150 --> 00:30:21,403
but it's a very private, intimate matter.

399
00:30:30,621 --> 00:30:31,455
What is it?

400
00:30:31,789 --> 00:30:32,665
Spit it out!

401
00:30:35,167 --> 00:30:38,837
I think there's something
going on between these two.

402
00:31:00,317 --> 00:31:01,777
You nutcase!

403
00:31:05,990 --> 00:31:08,617
He thought I was blinded by ambition?

404
00:31:12,538 --> 00:31:13,664
He greatly

405
00:31:14,206 --> 00:31:15,666
overestimated me.

406
00:31:17,751 --> 00:31:18,627
I'm just going to

407
00:31:19,962 --> 00:31:21,589
stick around this company long and steady

408
00:31:22,590 --> 00:31:24,091
like strands of naengmyeon noodles.

409
00:31:47,323 --> 00:31:48,782
Here's the salad you ordered.

410
00:31:48,866 --> 00:31:50,451
-Thank you.
-Thank you. Please enjoy.

411
00:31:53,454 --> 00:31:56,290
Sir, we work on fixed reservation times.

412
00:31:56,373 --> 00:31:58,584
I'm sorry, but may I take your order now?

413
00:31:59,460 --> 00:32:02,046
Yes. The dinner course, please.

414
00:32:02,129 --> 00:32:03,547
Would that be for one person?

415
00:32:06,634 --> 00:32:08,844
No, for two people.

416
00:32:08,927 --> 00:32:10,012
Of course, sir.

417
00:32:24,234 --> 00:32:25,069
You're here.

418
00:32:26,570 --> 00:32:27,529
Yes.

419
00:32:27,613 --> 00:32:30,282
I was about to look like someone
with a tragic backstory.

420
00:32:30,991 --> 00:32:32,159
Thanks for saving me.

421
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:34,953
What would you have done if I hadn't come?

422
00:32:35,037 --> 00:32:36,705
I'd have eaten alone and left.

423
00:32:37,665 --> 00:32:39,458
Then I'd have kept making reservations

424
00:32:40,042 --> 00:32:41,418
until you showed up, Ms. Ji-yoon.

425
00:32:47,424 --> 00:32:49,885
I'm here
because I want to ask you something.

426
00:32:51,095 --> 00:32:52,137
You can ask me anything.

427
00:32:52,680 --> 00:32:53,597
I'll answer you.

428
00:32:53,681 --> 00:32:54,640
Then,

429
00:32:55,849 --> 00:32:56,850
can you tell me

430
00:32:58,143 --> 00:33:01,188
the reason why you two got divorced?

431
00:33:03,399 --> 00:33:04,942
Where do you want me to start?

432
00:33:05,651 --> 00:33:08,237
From the very beginning to the end.

433
00:33:09,405 --> 00:33:10,280
All of it.

434
00:33:12,157 --> 00:33:13,200
Excuse me.

435
00:33:21,125 --> 00:33:22,042
Well,

436
00:33:22,668 --> 00:33:23,627
shall we eat first?

437
00:33:24,336 --> 00:33:25,212
Yes.

438
00:33:36,807 --> 00:33:39,393
Our mothers had been
best friends since high school.

439
00:33:40,269 --> 00:33:42,271
We saw each other a lot
since we were kids,

440
00:33:42,980 --> 00:33:46,775
and they'd joke all the time
about becoming in-laws one day.

441
00:33:46,859 --> 00:33:48,026
And then

442
00:33:49,236 --> 00:33:51,280
we ended up at the same college too

443
00:33:51,363 --> 00:33:52,823
and naturally started dating.

444
00:33:54,867 --> 00:33:56,160
We were an ordinary couple,

445
00:33:56,869 --> 00:33:59,663
and imagined a future together
like any ordinary couple would.

446
00:34:00,372 --> 00:34:01,749
So then,

447
00:34:01,832 --> 00:34:04,334
were you thinking
about marriage that far back?

448
00:34:04,418 --> 00:34:05,335
Yes.

449
00:34:06,503 --> 00:34:08,422
We were planning to study abroad together,

450
00:34:08,505 --> 00:34:10,174
so we got married right after graduation.

451
00:34:13,761 --> 00:34:14,803
But then

452
00:34:14,887 --> 00:34:17,347
my father's business suddenly went under,

453
00:34:17,431 --> 00:34:18,932
and my mother fell ill,

454
00:34:19,016 --> 00:34:20,934
so I was no longer able to go.

455
00:34:21,602 --> 00:34:23,979
And when Ms. Choi said she'd go alone,

456
00:34:24,980 --> 00:34:26,732
I couldn't bring myself to stop her.

457
00:34:27,316 --> 00:34:28,150
Why not?

458
00:34:29,568 --> 00:34:33,155
Aren't you supposed to make a choice
to stay together if you're married?

459
00:34:34,364 --> 00:34:36,575
Because I thought
that was the best for both of us.

460
00:34:39,536 --> 00:34:41,997
So I got a job to make money,

461
00:34:42,080 --> 00:34:45,083
and Ms. Choi went to the US to study.

462
00:34:45,667 --> 00:34:46,835
We both got busy,

463
00:34:47,878 --> 00:34:49,296
and there was a time difference,

464
00:34:50,255 --> 00:34:51,673
so we started talking less and less.

465
00:34:54,176 --> 00:34:56,011
Then my mother passed away,

466
00:34:56,094 --> 00:34:58,972
and when Ms. Choi
came back to Korea for a bit,

467
00:35:00,349 --> 00:35:01,683
she said she wanted a divorce.

468
00:35:03,894 --> 00:35:05,979
It felt like the obvious course of events.

469
00:35:06,063 --> 00:35:08,148
I was so exhausted from my own life

470
00:35:08,232 --> 00:35:12,027
that I had no room to tend to
the loneliness she was going through.

471
00:35:13,946 --> 00:35:15,656
So I agreed to what she said.

472
00:35:15,739 --> 00:35:17,783
It was less than a year

473
00:35:17,866 --> 00:35:19,743
from our wedding to our divorce.

474
00:35:22,454 --> 00:35:23,747
You went through all of that

475
00:35:25,332 --> 00:35:27,209
in just one year?

476
00:35:29,670 --> 00:35:30,546
Yes.

477
00:35:40,973 --> 00:35:42,516
I imagined it countless times.

478
00:35:43,559 --> 00:35:44,977
"How did those two meet?"

479
00:35:46,311 --> 00:35:47,604
"Was it love at first sight?"

480
00:35:48,647 --> 00:35:50,107
"Who fell first?"

481
00:35:51,775 --> 00:35:54,528
And I asked myself over and over,

482
00:35:56,363 --> 00:35:58,699
"Who was responsible for the split?"

483
00:36:00,492 --> 00:36:03,745
"If it was Mr. Kang's fault,

484
00:36:05,581 --> 00:36:07,749
could I handle that?"

485
00:36:10,252 --> 00:36:11,211
But

486
00:36:12,588 --> 00:36:15,591
I never imagined
you'd gone through things like that.

487
00:36:16,800 --> 00:36:19,678
The part of my past
that's so hard for you to shoulder

488
00:36:20,262 --> 00:36:22,097
was the emptiest time of my life.

489
00:36:23,557 --> 00:36:25,434
I don't want to be held back
by that time anymore.

490
00:36:27,144 --> 00:36:30,981
Now, every moment
I spend liking you feels too precious.

491
00:36:31,648 --> 00:36:33,567
Every minute, every second like this.

492
00:36:35,402 --> 00:36:36,403
I don't want

493
00:36:37,070 --> 00:36:38,488
to repeat

494
00:36:39,239 --> 00:36:40,490
the same mistake.

495
00:36:42,576 --> 00:36:45,120
I started this
because I have feelings for you,

496
00:36:46,330 --> 00:36:48,040
but feelings alone aren't enough now.

497
00:36:50,959 --> 00:36:52,377
If I were to be with you,

498
00:36:53,754 --> 00:36:57,049
I want to do it
when I'm sure I won't waver.

499
00:36:59,718 --> 00:37:00,886
Is that okay with you?

500
00:37:03,388 --> 00:37:04,348
Yes,

501
00:37:04,431 --> 00:37:05,390
of course.

502
00:37:45,263 --> 00:37:46,264
Good morning!

503
00:37:58,610 --> 00:37:59,486
Good morning.

504
00:38:16,211 --> 00:38:17,170
SET THE COOKING TIME

505
00:38:28,640 --> 00:38:30,017
STANDARD
DETERGENT, FABRIC SOFTENER

506
00:38:30,100 --> 00:38:33,520
My twin boys just won't listen to me.
What should I do?

507
00:38:35,063 --> 00:38:36,606
SEE WHAT'S GOING ON
AND GIVE THEM ATTENTION

508
00:38:36,690 --> 00:38:38,567
And how do I give them attention?

509
00:38:38,650 --> 00:38:39,568
No.

510
00:38:41,987 --> 00:38:43,530
It can't be pushed back even by a day.

511
00:39:19,941 --> 00:39:20,776
Hello.

512
00:39:39,711 --> 00:39:40,545
Where's Mr. Kang?

513
00:39:41,129 --> 00:39:43,215
-He said he was going to the hospital.
-Why?

514
00:39:43,298 --> 00:39:45,133
All that overtime must've gotten to him.

515
00:39:51,306 --> 00:39:53,391
MANAGER KANG SI-WOO

516
00:40:03,151 --> 00:40:04,152
What's wrong?

517
00:40:05,445 --> 00:40:06,279
Huh?

518
00:40:06,363 --> 00:40:08,115
You look really worried.

519
00:40:11,201 --> 00:40:12,869
Mr. Kang's gone to the hospital.

520
00:40:13,829 --> 00:40:14,996
I was wondering if he's okay.

521
00:40:16,665 --> 00:40:17,874
Did you give him a call?

522
00:40:19,584 --> 00:40:20,418
No.

523
00:40:20,919 --> 00:40:22,170
Why not? Just call him.

524
00:40:22,754 --> 00:40:24,297
I actually asked him

525
00:40:25,048 --> 00:40:26,925
to give me some time.

526
00:40:27,425 --> 00:40:28,635
Did something happen?

527
00:40:29,845 --> 00:40:32,389
I just lost my confidence.

528
00:40:34,141 --> 00:40:35,642
You feel that way too?

529
00:40:37,352 --> 00:40:39,312
I thought I was the only one
who has no confidence.

530
00:40:41,982 --> 00:40:44,359
I guess there's no such thing
as an easy relationship.

531
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:47,320
Work at least gets a bit easier
as you gain experience.

532
00:40:48,029 --> 00:40:49,906
Why is love so difficult all the time?

533
00:40:49,990 --> 00:40:53,910
The fact that someone as smart as you
also becomes a fool when it comes to love

534
00:40:54,452 --> 00:40:56,288
is oddly reassuring to me.

535
00:40:56,371 --> 00:40:58,707
I'm completely hopeless at this.

536
00:41:35,785 --> 00:41:36,828
KANG SI-WOO

537
00:41:36,912 --> 00:41:38,496
Did you enjoy your lunch?

538
00:41:47,380 --> 00:41:49,382
Are you feeling all right?

539
00:41:51,426 --> 00:41:52,427
Yes,

540
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:54,012
I got better after an IV.

541
00:41:55,764 --> 00:41:57,974
I thought you said
you take good care of yourself.

542
00:41:58,058 --> 00:41:59,768
We can't have our team lead fall sick.

543
00:42:01,770 --> 00:42:04,564
It's kind of nice
being sick once in a while.

544
00:42:09,486 --> 00:42:11,112
Look after yourself first, okay?

545
00:42:14,199 --> 00:42:16,201
I even like hearing you nag.

546
00:42:25,669 --> 00:42:27,879
The brochures are here!

547
00:42:28,797 --> 00:42:30,257
This one's for Mr. Kang.

548
00:42:30,340 --> 00:42:31,591
And this one's for Ms. Cha.

549
00:42:36,304 --> 00:42:38,682
They look great. Nice work.

550
00:42:38,765 --> 00:42:39,599
Thank you.

551
00:42:40,850 --> 00:42:41,726
Tomorrow's the big day.

552
00:42:43,061 --> 00:42:45,605
Let's make sure we showcase
everything we've prepared.

553
00:42:46,690 --> 00:42:48,233
But what about that other thing?

554
00:42:48,316 --> 00:42:49,693
What thing?

555
00:42:49,776 --> 00:42:51,069
The Demo Ghost.

556
00:42:53,863 --> 00:42:54,781
"Demo Ghost"?

557
00:42:55,657 --> 00:42:58,076
I guess you don't know
because you were in the US.

558
00:42:58,159 --> 00:42:59,327
There's this ghost

559
00:42:59,411 --> 00:43:02,122
that shows up at demos
no matter how many times you rehearse.

560
00:43:02,664 --> 00:43:04,874
It makes sparkling water
not come out of the cooler,

561
00:43:04,958 --> 00:43:07,669
breaks voice recognition
that was working perfectly,

562
00:43:07,752 --> 00:43:10,672
and even freezes robot vacuum cleaners
that were working fine,

563
00:43:10,755 --> 00:43:12,299
or so the legend goes.

564
00:43:13,049 --> 00:43:14,759
I've never seen it myself.

565
00:43:14,843 --> 00:43:16,928
A lot of errors happen
every time we do a demo,

566
00:43:17,012 --> 00:43:18,596
so we just say it's the ghost's doing.

567
00:43:20,265 --> 00:43:21,349
Should we use a talisman?

568
00:43:21,433 --> 00:43:22,809
I'm the talisman.

569
00:43:23,852 --> 00:43:26,521
Stop worrying and go home early today.

570
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:28,231
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

571
00:43:42,495 --> 00:43:44,205
Turn in early tonight

572
00:43:44,289 --> 00:43:46,458
so that you'll be ready to handle
any ghost that shows up.

573
00:43:50,503 --> 00:43:51,421
You too, Mr. Kang.

574
00:43:59,429 --> 00:44:01,389
For years,

575
00:44:01,473 --> 00:44:05,310
we've been creating home appliances
that make people's lives easier.

576
00:44:05,393 --> 00:44:06,895
And today,

577
00:44:06,978 --> 00:44:09,564
that technology
takes another step forward.

578
00:44:09,647 --> 00:44:11,483
Meet "Home-AI."

579
00:44:11,566 --> 00:44:13,777
Now, please experience that future

580
00:44:14,903 --> 00:44:15,945
for yourself.

581
00:44:21,493 --> 00:44:23,078
Now, shall we see

582
00:44:23,161 --> 00:44:26,289
how much Home-AI can change your day

583
00:44:26,373 --> 00:44:28,416
by following a busy day in Seoul?

584
00:44:33,922 --> 00:44:35,465
In the morning,

585
00:44:35,548 --> 00:44:37,217
the first thing you do is check

586
00:44:37,300 --> 00:44:40,220
your schedule and the weather
on the refrigerator screen

587
00:44:40,303 --> 00:44:43,723
so that you can pick your outfit
according to those two factors.

588
00:44:53,525 --> 00:44:54,776
But on the way to work,

589
00:44:54,859 --> 00:44:57,904
you remember
you didn't turn off the induction cooktop.

590
00:44:57,987 --> 00:45:00,240
In the old days,
that would've meant running late.

591
00:45:00,323 --> 00:45:01,658
But now,

592
00:45:01,741 --> 00:45:04,244
you can turn it off
by remote control on your phone.

593
00:45:04,327 --> 00:45:05,870
COOKTOP
OFF

594
00:45:12,043 --> 00:45:14,129
While working at the office,

595
00:45:14,212 --> 00:45:16,631
if you suddenly wonder
how your dog is doing,

596
00:45:17,340 --> 00:45:20,218
you can check the video
your robot vacuum cleaner sends you.

597
00:45:20,301 --> 00:45:21,136
Here's Sun-shim.

598
00:45:22,804 --> 00:45:25,306
Sure enough, Sun-shim is napping again.

599
00:45:35,942 --> 00:45:39,612
After a long day at work,
you come home and start preparing dinner.

600
00:45:39,696 --> 00:45:42,198
Maybe you'll try a new recipe tonight.

601
00:45:42,282 --> 00:45:43,408
CHICKEN STEAK,

602
00:45:43,491 --> 00:45:47,412
You search for recipes you can make
with ingredients in your fridge

603
00:45:47,495 --> 00:45:48,872
send the one you chose to the oven,

604
00:45:49,539 --> 00:45:52,000
put all the prepped ingredients
into the oven, and voilà. Dinner's ready.

605
00:46:05,597 --> 00:46:07,348
Once you're finished with your dinner,

606
00:46:07,432 --> 00:46:09,893
it's time to do
one of your least favorite chores.

607
00:46:09,976 --> 00:46:11,394
The laundry.

608
00:46:17,066 --> 00:46:18,860
Washing machine, open the door.

609
00:46:34,542 --> 00:46:37,420
1 SELECTED
FRIDGE

610
00:46:43,051 --> 00:46:44,135
It's the Demo Ghost.

611
00:47:26,302 --> 00:47:27,387
What's that punk doing?

612
00:47:36,187 --> 00:47:37,897
The age of Home-AI has arrived.

613
00:47:38,565 --> 00:47:40,650
Our devices are now smarter than ever,

614
00:47:40,733 --> 00:47:42,360
and they have learned our preferences,

615
00:47:42,443 --> 00:47:44,237
our lifestyle, our medical data,

616
00:47:44,320 --> 00:47:46,239
and even our voices.

617
00:47:47,073 --> 00:47:49,242
But if something like this happens,

618
00:47:49,325 --> 00:47:52,412
we would not be able
to trust and use Home-AI.

619
00:47:55,498 --> 00:47:56,541
Mr. Lee.

620
00:47:56,624 --> 00:47:57,458
Yes?

621
00:47:57,542 --> 00:47:59,836
Did you hack this system?

622
00:48:00,420 --> 00:48:01,254
I did.

623
00:48:03,006 --> 00:48:05,508
I hacked it
and planted a bug in the system.

624
00:48:07,302 --> 00:48:10,138
Then personal data
could be leaked too, right?

625
00:48:10,471 --> 00:48:11,306
Yes,

626
00:48:11,973 --> 00:48:12,974
very much so.

627
00:48:17,895 --> 00:48:18,938
What the heck is going on?

628
00:48:20,106 --> 00:48:21,274
I'm not sure. I…

629
00:48:31,075 --> 00:48:32,785
Manager Ko and Managing Director Noh?

630
00:48:32,869 --> 00:48:33,870
Yes.

631
00:48:34,454 --> 00:48:36,748
They told me
to sabotage the demo by any means.

632
00:48:36,831 --> 00:48:38,041
What did they offer you in return?

633
00:48:38,124 --> 00:48:39,751
Your position.

634
00:48:39,834 --> 00:48:42,295
They said they'd make me
the team lead of the task force.

635
00:48:43,004 --> 00:48:46,007
So they're planning to swallow the Future
Household Appliances Task Force whole.

636
00:48:46,090 --> 00:48:47,300
They said if the demo failed,

637
00:48:48,051 --> 00:48:50,011
the task force would report
directly to the Vice President

638
00:48:50,094 --> 00:48:52,639
and that Mr. Noh
would manage it himself.

639
00:48:57,060 --> 00:48:58,853
That must've been pretty tempting to you.

640
00:49:01,814 --> 00:49:02,649
Not at all.

641
00:49:04,692 --> 00:49:07,153
"Let your work speak for itself,
not politics."

642
00:49:07,236 --> 00:49:09,656
"Work for yourself, not someone else."

643
00:49:11,240 --> 00:49:14,452
I never forgot what I learned from you.

644
00:49:20,249 --> 00:49:21,250
Then…

645
00:49:22,627 --> 00:49:24,337
Do exactly as Mr. Noh says.

646
00:49:24,420 --> 00:49:25,254
Sorry?

647
00:49:26,214 --> 00:49:28,883
You attack,
and I'll try to defend against it.

648
00:49:34,055 --> 00:49:35,848
That's why we made security

649
00:49:35,932 --> 00:49:38,351
the top priority of our Home-AI project.

650
00:49:38,434 --> 00:49:40,436
And finally, we've developed

651
00:49:41,979 --> 00:49:43,856
our new security program,
Neo Solution.

652
00:49:51,322 --> 00:49:52,407
RESTORE

653
00:49:55,785 --> 00:49:59,080
Neo Solution doesn't just
fix malicious programs.

654
00:49:59,163 --> 00:50:01,374
It uses blockchain technology
so that all connected devices

655
00:50:01,457 --> 00:50:03,793
can protect one another
from security threats.

656
00:50:04,377 --> 00:50:07,296
If there's an issue
with one device, it gets isolated

657
00:50:07,380 --> 00:50:09,215
so that the rest of Home-AI stays secure.

658
00:50:10,883 --> 00:50:12,635
Sensitive information
is stored separately,

659
00:50:12,719 --> 00:50:14,929
which gives it
multiple layers of protection.

660
00:50:16,723 --> 00:50:19,976
Creating a world that is tailored
to each user's unique lifestyle.

661
00:50:22,019 --> 00:50:25,732
We've named this kind
of user experience "Home-AI."

662
00:51:13,362 --> 00:51:14,614
What just happened?

663
00:51:14,697 --> 00:51:17,325
Well, to put it simply,

664
00:51:17,408 --> 00:51:18,743
I was a double agent.

665
00:51:19,327 --> 00:51:20,244
Pardon?

666
00:51:20,328 --> 00:51:22,205
Are you kidding me?

667
00:51:22,288 --> 00:51:23,247
Unbelievable!

668
00:51:23,873 --> 00:51:25,833
Looks like Lee Young-hun turned on us.

669
00:51:26,334 --> 00:51:28,628
I know. I clearly misjudged.

670
00:51:28,711 --> 00:51:30,338
-Probably a month ago.
-A month?

671
00:51:30,421 --> 00:51:31,798
I didn't expect this from him.

672
00:51:32,340 --> 00:51:34,091
No, I misjudged you.

673
00:51:34,175 --> 00:51:36,219
You useless punk.

674
00:51:37,178 --> 00:51:38,054
Get lost.

675
00:51:40,932 --> 00:51:41,891
Mr. Noh.

676
00:51:43,476 --> 00:51:44,644
To make it neat…

677
00:51:44,727 --> 00:51:45,645
Choi Soo-jin.

678
00:51:47,063 --> 00:51:48,064
Jeong Hyeon-u!

679
00:51:50,942 --> 00:51:52,693
That's right, your college classmate.

680
00:51:52,777 --> 00:51:55,905
I heard you went abroad after graduation.
I can't believe we're meeting here.

681
00:51:55,988 --> 00:51:57,615
And I heard you two got married.

682
00:51:58,407 --> 00:52:00,743
But I didn't know you and Si-woo
work at the same company.

683
00:52:01,953 --> 00:52:03,120
How's working with your husband?

684
00:52:03,204 --> 00:52:04,747
Well, about that…

685
00:52:04,831 --> 00:52:05,665
Ms. Choi.

686
00:52:05,748 --> 00:52:07,208
President Han is looking for you.

687
00:52:07,291 --> 00:52:08,417
Okay.

688
00:52:09,085 --> 00:52:10,127
Let's talk later.

689
00:52:10,211 --> 00:52:12,463
Sure, the three of us should grab a meal.

690
00:52:13,422 --> 00:52:14,590
-See you.
-Yeah.

691
00:52:27,144 --> 00:52:28,938
Luck's finally on my side!

692
00:52:31,274 --> 00:52:33,526
To the Future Household Appliances
Task Force,

693
00:52:33,609 --> 00:52:36,153
who just finished a successful demo!

694
00:52:36,237 --> 00:52:38,364
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

695
00:52:39,198 --> 00:52:40,908
Mr. Kang! Over here!

696
00:52:41,534 --> 00:52:43,703
-Another draft beer, please!
-Coming!

697
00:52:47,331 --> 00:52:49,417
I thought you went
to dinner with the buyers.

698
00:52:49,500 --> 00:52:51,043
I just stopped by to say hello.

699
00:52:51,127 --> 00:52:53,254
The Global Sales Team
can take it from there.

700
00:52:53,337 --> 00:52:55,381
But still, shouldn't you be there?

701
00:52:55,464 --> 00:52:57,508
This is more important to me.

702
00:52:58,301 --> 00:52:59,969
Great work today, everyone.

703
00:53:00,678 --> 00:53:02,930
That was so cruel, Mr. Kang.

704
00:53:03,014 --> 00:53:07,101
You almost gave all of us a heart attack.
We could've died!

705
00:53:07,184 --> 00:53:09,604
I had to do it
to fool the other side completely.

706
00:53:09,687 --> 00:53:11,522
-I hope you understand.
-Of course.

707
00:53:14,025 --> 00:53:15,359
I'm sorry.

708
00:53:16,652 --> 00:53:20,781
Truth is,
I actually got an offer from Mr. Ko too.

709
00:53:21,324 --> 00:53:23,409
He said he'd make me a Sr. Associate

710
00:53:25,077 --> 00:53:26,829
if I gave him your weakness, Mr. Kang.

711
00:53:27,788 --> 00:53:28,789
For real?

712
00:53:29,373 --> 00:53:30,583
So what did you give him?

713
00:53:32,126 --> 00:53:32,960
A juicy rumor…

714
00:53:35,212 --> 00:53:38,966
involving a romantic scandal
between Mr. Kang and Mr. Lee.

715
00:53:42,053 --> 00:53:43,679
You know, to get him off my back.

716
00:53:49,727 --> 00:53:51,187
But to be honest,

717
00:53:52,605 --> 00:53:54,774
I was really tempted by the offer.

718
00:53:55,650 --> 00:53:57,109
I've been an Associate forever

719
00:53:57,860 --> 00:53:59,153
with twins to feed.

720
00:54:01,739 --> 00:54:02,949
I understand.

721
00:54:03,532 --> 00:54:06,994
Work is where you keep
getting your limits tested.

722
00:54:08,120 --> 00:54:09,705
But if you didn't give in,

723
00:54:09,789 --> 00:54:12,625
that means you didn't give up on yourself.

724
00:54:14,502 --> 00:54:17,546
How do you always say such cool things?

725
00:54:21,258 --> 00:54:22,259
Whatever, okay?

726
00:54:22,343 --> 00:54:24,220
I love the task force!

727
00:54:24,303 --> 00:54:25,972
We're together forever!

728
00:54:26,055 --> 00:54:27,640
-Forever!
-Forever!

729
00:54:28,683 --> 00:54:30,101
I'm returning to the Development Team.

730
00:54:30,184 --> 00:54:31,227
What?

731
00:54:31,310 --> 00:54:33,646
I thought you were
staying with us until launch.

732
00:54:33,729 --> 00:54:36,524
My part here in the task force is done.

733
00:54:36,607 --> 00:54:38,317
Time to move on to the next thing.

734
00:54:38,401 --> 00:54:42,029
This company
never gives us a single break,

735
00:54:42,113 --> 00:54:42,947
does it?

736
00:54:43,030 --> 00:54:44,448
We get paid, so we work.

737
00:54:45,116 --> 00:54:46,283
Mr. Kang!

738
00:54:46,367 --> 00:54:49,537
You should side with us
at least for today.

739
00:54:50,997 --> 00:54:51,831
But still,

740
00:54:51,914 --> 00:54:53,082
we're together forever.

741
00:54:55,001 --> 00:54:57,420
-Forever!
-Forever!

742
00:55:06,137 --> 00:55:07,221
Did you wait for long?

743
00:55:07,304 --> 00:55:10,016
No, I got here right on time.
Did it go well today?

744
00:55:10,099 --> 00:55:12,601
Yeah, I got a ton of compliments.

745
00:55:12,685 --> 00:55:13,978
It's the first time

746
00:55:14,061 --> 00:55:16,105
I've been recognized at work
for my own effort.

747
00:55:16,188 --> 00:55:18,357
Are you about to get promoted right away?

748
00:55:18,441 --> 00:55:19,734
Not even close.

749
00:55:20,443 --> 00:55:21,277
I'm hungry.

750
00:55:21,861 --> 00:55:22,945
Let's go eat.

751
00:55:26,574 --> 00:55:27,575
No-ah!

752
00:55:32,830 --> 00:55:33,664
Hi.

753
00:55:34,707 --> 00:55:35,541
Who's this?

754
00:55:45,593 --> 00:55:46,510
My boyfriend.

755
00:55:46,594 --> 00:55:47,678
Really?

756
00:55:48,220 --> 00:55:49,055
That's awesome.

757
00:55:51,348 --> 00:55:53,559
We have to go eat,
so let's catch up later.

758
00:55:53,642 --> 00:55:54,518
Yeah.

759
00:56:00,691 --> 00:56:02,735
Word will spread everywhere
now that they know.

760
00:56:02,818 --> 00:56:03,778
Can you handle that?

761
00:56:03,861 --> 00:56:05,154
Then you handle this too.

762
00:56:05,821 --> 00:56:08,240
-Huh?
-I'm Yoon No-ah's boyfriend!

763
00:56:10,618 --> 00:56:12,286
I'm Yoon No-ah's boyfriend!

764
00:56:17,083 --> 00:56:18,334
Wait for me, girlfriend!

765
00:56:19,543 --> 00:56:21,003
I really loved this task force.

766
00:56:21,087 --> 00:56:22,421
You worked so hard.

767
00:56:24,131 --> 00:56:26,217
-Where's Mr. Kang?
-He left early.

768
00:56:26,300 --> 00:56:27,134
What?

769
00:56:27,551 --> 00:56:29,512
He seemed really exhausted.

770
00:56:31,138 --> 00:56:33,349
He probably hasn't been sleeping much.

771
00:56:34,058 --> 00:56:36,727
He was buried
in that security solution for months.

772
00:56:38,020 --> 00:56:39,688
Doesn't Mr. Kang live alone?

773
00:56:40,147 --> 00:56:40,981
I'm heading out first.

774
00:56:41,065 --> 00:56:43,442
It's doubly miserable
if you're alone when you're sick.

775
00:56:44,985 --> 00:56:47,655
Actually, I think I should head out too.

776
00:56:47,738 --> 00:56:49,949
-Why, all of a sudden?
-My mom…

777
00:56:50,032 --> 00:56:52,076
No, my dad got injured, and…

778
00:56:52,159 --> 00:56:53,160
Hey!

779
00:56:53,661 --> 00:56:55,079
You should hurry and go to your father.

780
00:56:55,162 --> 00:56:56,372
Yeah,

781
00:56:56,455 --> 00:56:57,790
-I should.
-Yeah.

782
00:56:57,873 --> 00:57:00,417
-I'll be in touch later.
-Yes, go ahead.

783
00:57:00,501 --> 00:57:02,128
-All right, then. Good night.
-Yes.

784
00:57:02,211 --> 00:57:03,295
Get going, quick!

785
00:57:04,463 --> 00:57:05,881
She's just leaving like that?

786
00:57:05,965 --> 00:57:06,924
Well, her father's injured.

787
00:57:07,007 --> 00:57:08,342
-Hey, let's drink.
-Sure.

788
00:57:22,064 --> 00:57:23,399
Is he not home?

789
00:57:46,589 --> 00:57:47,548
Mr. Kang.

790
00:57:50,217 --> 00:57:51,051
Mr. Kang?

791
00:57:53,262 --> 00:57:54,555
Mr. Kang!

792
00:57:56,599 --> 00:57:57,433
Mr. Kang!

793
00:57:58,309 --> 00:57:59,268
Mr. Kang!

794
00:58:01,896 --> 00:58:03,147
Mr. Kang!

795
00:58:06,233 --> 00:58:07,109
Ms. Ji-yoon?

796
00:58:12,573 --> 00:58:14,033
Where the heck were you?

797
00:58:14,533 --> 00:58:16,493
You scared me. I thought you passed out.

798
00:58:17,286 --> 00:58:19,371
I might pass out from you hitting me.

799
00:58:20,789 --> 00:58:22,541
I was so worried.

800
00:58:30,216 --> 00:58:31,675
How could I possibly

801
00:58:32,301 --> 00:58:33,719
give up someone like you?

802
00:58:46,815 --> 00:58:47,816
Have some tea.

803
00:59:02,289 --> 00:59:03,749
There's something I want to ask.

804
00:59:04,500 --> 00:59:05,834
You still have more questions?

805
00:59:07,002 --> 00:59:10,047
Why did you tell me from the beginning

806
00:59:11,423 --> 00:59:13,550
that Ms. Choi is your ex-wife?

807
00:59:16,262 --> 00:59:17,179
I don't know.

808
00:59:19,056 --> 00:59:22,768
It's definitely not something
I would normally share.

809
00:59:23,644 --> 00:59:24,728
Maybe it was a system error,

810
00:59:24,812 --> 00:59:27,648
since you're the only variable
that changes me.

811
00:59:30,859 --> 00:59:32,653
I don't know why I said it,

812
00:59:32,736 --> 00:59:34,280
but after I fell for you,

813
00:59:34,947 --> 00:59:37,116
I was glad I'd already told you about it.

814
00:59:38,367 --> 00:59:39,201
Pathetic, right?

815
00:59:40,786 --> 00:59:41,620
Yes.

816
00:59:43,247 --> 00:59:46,208
I want us to think things through together

817
00:59:46,875 --> 00:59:47,960
and take responsibility together.

818
00:59:50,754 --> 00:59:51,588
Let's do that.

819
00:59:51,672 --> 00:59:54,466
Don't hide things,
saying it's for my sake.

820
00:59:55,092 --> 00:59:55,926
Tell me everything.

821
00:59:57,177 --> 00:59:58,095
I will.

822
01:00:00,097 --> 01:00:02,975
Then be honest with me.

823
01:00:06,937 --> 01:00:08,230
Wasn't it hard?

824
01:00:12,985 --> 01:00:14,695
Wasn't it painful…

825
01:00:16,822 --> 01:00:17,906
being alone for so long?

826
01:00:29,960 --> 01:00:30,919
Yes.

827
01:00:33,255 --> 01:00:34,214
It was painful.

828
01:00:41,764 --> 01:00:43,766
When my father's business went under

829
01:00:43,849 --> 01:00:46,060
and left my mother
as if he were running away…

830
01:01:04,161 --> 01:01:08,290
When Ms. Choi left
to go study abroad by herself…

831
01:01:14,671 --> 01:01:17,841
Even when she asked to get a divorce…

832
01:01:17,925 --> 01:01:19,385
I couldn't stop it.

833
01:01:21,095 --> 01:01:24,264
I told myself that letting go
was the considerate thing to do.

834
01:01:25,766 --> 01:01:26,683
But really,

835
01:01:27,643 --> 01:01:28,811
it was just my pride

836
01:01:30,687 --> 01:01:33,440
not wanting to admit how unhappy

837
01:01:34,233 --> 01:01:35,859
and lonely I was.

838
01:01:37,277 --> 01:01:38,445
Back then,

839
01:01:39,530 --> 01:01:42,032
I didn't know how to share grief.

840
01:01:45,911 --> 01:01:47,287
You were even younger

841
01:01:48,622 --> 01:01:50,499
than I am right now.

842
01:01:53,252 --> 01:01:54,336
How did you…

843
01:01:56,672 --> 01:01:59,216
handle all of that sadness by yourself?

844
01:02:07,766 --> 01:02:09,059
I feel so sorry

845
01:02:10,519 --> 01:02:11,645
for the past you.

846
01:02:28,328 --> 01:02:29,371
You're in trouble.

847
01:02:30,539 --> 01:02:32,040
They say it's game over if you feel pity.

848
01:02:32,749 --> 01:02:33,750
Your past

849
01:02:34,626 --> 01:02:36,920
doesn't matter to me at all anymore.

850
01:02:40,007 --> 01:02:41,425
No matter how temperamental

851
01:02:42,718 --> 01:02:43,927
or how romantic you may be…

852
01:02:47,598 --> 01:02:48,515
I'm just

853
01:02:49,641 --> 01:02:52,436
going to focus
on my feelings for you right now.

854
01:02:56,690 --> 01:02:57,608
See?

855
01:02:58,192 --> 01:03:01,153
I told you it won't be easy
to turn me down.

856
01:03:05,616 --> 01:03:07,201
Can I take back what I just said?

857
01:03:09,203 --> 01:03:10,037
Nope.

858
01:03:12,289 --> 01:03:16,084
Forget my pride.
I won't let go of you no matter what.

859
01:04:01,713 --> 01:04:02,756
Shall we go for a walk?

860
01:04:03,507 --> 01:04:04,675
Sorry?

861
01:04:04,758 --> 01:04:07,886
I don't like doing this
just to blow off emotions.

862
01:04:11,014 --> 01:04:12,266
Okay, then…

863
01:04:12,349 --> 01:04:13,267
Then?

864
01:04:14,101 --> 01:04:15,686
Buy me some steamed buns.

865
01:04:16,270 --> 01:04:18,397
-Steamed buns?
-Yes.

866
01:04:18,480 --> 01:04:20,899
I haven't had
my first steamed bun of the year yet.

867
01:04:42,296 --> 01:04:43,171
Found it.

868
01:04:51,638 --> 01:04:55,267
A COLLEGE COUPLE SUCCESS STORY!
YOU TWO HAPPY TO GET MARRIED?

869
01:04:56,101 --> 01:04:57,436
You should have some too.

870
01:04:58,228 --> 01:04:59,896
I don't do carbs this late, so…

871
01:04:59,980 --> 01:05:02,524
Fine! I'll be the only one getting fat.

872
01:05:04,276 --> 01:05:05,652
Your hands are all red. Here.

873
01:05:05,736 --> 01:05:06,695
I'll hold it.

874
01:05:14,620 --> 01:05:15,787
Gosh, that's hot!

875
01:05:17,914 --> 01:05:18,749
Ms. Ji-yoon.

876
01:05:19,541 --> 01:05:20,375
Yes?

877
01:05:23,003 --> 01:05:23,837
I love you.

878
01:05:36,642 --> 01:05:38,727
You're saying that
with a steamed bun in your hands?

879
01:05:39,186 --> 01:05:40,312
I may be holding a steamed bun,

880
01:05:41,063 --> 01:05:42,147
but I mean it.

881
01:05:45,984 --> 01:05:46,860
I do too.

882
01:05:49,196 --> 01:05:50,030
What did you say?

883
01:05:52,366 --> 01:05:53,659
I love you.

884
01:06:12,552 --> 01:06:13,553
It's snowing.

885
01:06:17,432 --> 01:06:19,559
Mr. Kang, it's snowing!

886
01:06:24,648 --> 01:06:26,566
At last, I found my happiness again.

887
01:06:27,818 --> 01:06:30,028
May it last

888
01:06:30,904 --> 01:06:33,407
for a very long time.

889
01:06:57,264 --> 01:06:59,683
SPECIAL THANKS TO BAE YU-RAM

890
01:07:21,788 --> 01:07:24,708
WE'RE A TEAM!

891
01:07:28,462 --> 01:07:30,839
Wait, is this a proposal?

892
01:07:31,590 --> 01:07:32,883
I used to think

893
01:07:32,966 --> 01:07:36,219
that marriage
was the natural ending to dating.

894
01:07:36,303 --> 01:07:38,764
Then why am I hesitating now?

895
01:07:39,347 --> 01:07:41,975
Married couples fight. It's inevitable.

896
01:07:42,058 --> 01:07:43,810
I don't like having stuff lying around.

897
01:07:44,394 --> 01:07:45,604
What's all this?

898
01:07:45,687 --> 01:07:47,731
Those two were actually married?

899
01:07:47,814 --> 01:07:49,858
What if someone
spread this rumor with ill intent?

900
01:07:50,442 --> 01:07:51,985
What happened?

901
01:07:52,068 --> 01:07:54,404
I may not be able
to lift you up the ladder,

902
01:07:54,488 --> 01:07:56,656
but I can drag you straight to the bottom!

903
01:08:02,245 --> 01:08:04,247
Subtitle: Yenny Kang
